<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FFC46A7BF82390D71426BC7F" pageId="63" pageNumber="821" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFFC46A7BF82390D71426BC7F" blockId="63.[2012,2607,1607,2026]" pageId="63" pageNumber="821">
Often treated in 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFC46A7BF73090D7174CBD9D" authorityName="Kaup" authorityYear="1829" box="[2252,2380,1678,1711]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Pipistrellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="821" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pipistrellus</taxonomicName>
, sometimes in a subgenus (typically 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFC46A7BF70890EC175DBDE4" box="[2292,2397,1717,1750]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="821" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Hypsugo</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFC46A7BF66790EC1421BDE4" authorityName="Kaup" authorityYear="1829" box="[2459,2593,1717,1750]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Pipistrellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="821" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pipistrellus</taxonomicName>
); due to its nyctalodont lower molars. This species might include a complex and clearly needs revision. Seven subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
